Daud Olatunji Ogun State Governor  Dapo Abiodun has told his  political  appointees to be ready to  work for the state. Abiodun spoke   at a two- day Executive Council Strategy Session  on Saturday at Ogere, Ikenne Local Government Area of the state. He said, “It is time to work. It is important to gather, to explore and formalise the various opportunities in the implementation of our building our future together agenda and take the advantage of the abundant resources in the state. “Your creativity and experience have started to manifest positively in your various ministries, department and agencies. You are to partner and ensure the development of the state and increase  the prosperity of our people, irrespective of age, gender, political affiliation and locations.” Abiodun said the retreat would serve as a platform to exchange ideas and come up with practical approaches to the discharge of good governance. Speaking on a topic,  ‘Overview of the Nigerian Macro-economic Economic Environment- Key Implications for Ogun State’, the  Chairman, Nigeria Economic Advisory Council, Dr Doyin Salami, and a financial expert, Mr Bismarck Rewane,  said   for the state to witness any meaningful economic development, the government  must   reduce  cost of governance by 15 per cent. Copyright PUNCH.
